Suspenses: (noun) Unreported personal savings for special occasions.

Suspenses may be far more familiar to people than they know. Suspenses is a new phrase sure to get into Oxford eventually. 

"Suspenses" is the combination of two words - "Suspicious" and "Expenses". Suspenses are therefore the suspicious expenses one accumulates to gain extra money for spending when someone (spouse, parent, lover, etc) doesn't need to know.

Suspenses accounts are savings tucked away for special occasions. You contribute to your suspense account by skimming money off of a purchase. Ex. You are supposed to buy groceries for $50 but find it comes to only $37. You pocket the $13 in your suspenses account for future use and report the actual spending of $50.